to the EC BU department and cadets  The result has been a marked increase in the number and quality of internships  Taking the internship program a step further  this past winter the academic board approved the department s proposal to give up to three credit hours in either economics or business to internships that meet particular academic standards  Overseen and approved by internship advisor Lt  Col Bob Moreschi and department head Col  Floyd Duncan  qualifying internships must be rigorous in nature  Cadets are required to write a term paper and give a presentation to the department faculty  Five cadets are participating this summer  at firms such as Ernst   Young and Owens   Minor  Spring 2007 Newsletter  AACSB Accreditation  Field Test BU  Mission Statement  New Faculty Faces  New Book Released  Faculty Research  Speakers  Engineering Initiative  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  Class of 2005  Cadet Field Trip  Cadet Awards  Hinman Award  Stay Connected  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 